SIMPLE: since
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Since
<hw>Since</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧ns)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>sins</ets>, contr. fr. OE. <ets>sithens</ets>, <ets>sithenes</ets>,
formed by an adverbial ending (cf. <er>Besides</er>) from OE.
<ets>sithen</ets>, also shortened into <ets>sithe</ets>, <ets>sin</ets>,
AS. <ets>si⟦edh⟧⟦edh⟧an</ets>, <ets>sy⟦edh⟧⟦edh⟧an</ets>,
<ets>seo⟦edh⟧⟦edh⟧an</ets>, afterward, then, since, after; properly,
after that; fr. <ets>s⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets> after, later, adv. and prep.
(originally a comparative adv., akin to OS. <ets>s⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>
afterward, since, OHG. <ets>s⟦imac⟧d</ets>, G. <ets>seit</ets> since,
Goth. <ets>sei⟦thorn⟧us</ets> late, ni ⟦thorn⟧ana<ets>sei⟦thorn⟧s</ets>
no longer) + <ets>⟦edh⟧on</ets> instrumental of the demonstrative and
article. See <er>That</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>From a definite past
time until now; <as>as, he went a month ago, and I have not seen him
<ex>since</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We <qex>since</qex> become the slaves to one man's lust.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the time past, counting backward from the
present; before this or now; ago.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How many ages <qex>since</qex> has Virgil writ?</q>
<rj><qau>Roscommon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>About two years <qex>since</qex>, it so fell out, that he was
brought to a great lady's house.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>When or that.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Do you remember <qex>since</qex> we lay all night in the windmill
in St. George's field?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Since</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Since
<hw>Since</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>From the time of; in or during the
time subsequent to; subsequently to; after; -- usually with a past event
or time for the object.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Lord hath blessed thee, <qex>since</qex> my coming.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xxx. 30.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a model by which he build a nobler poem than any extant
<qex>since</qex> the ancients.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Since</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Since
<hw>Since</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>Seeing that; because; considering;
-- formerly followed by <xex>that</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Since</qex> that my penitence comes after all,⟦br⟧
Imploring pardon.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Since</qex> truth and constancy are vain,⟦br⟧
<qex>Since</qex> neither love, nor sense of pain,⟦br⟧
Nor force of reason, can persuade,⟦br⟧
Then let example be obeyed.</q> <rj><qau>Granville.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Because; for; as; inasmuch as; considering. See
<er>Because</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sincere</ent>⟦br⟧
